OL,6,FFrom 2014 to 2015, MacDonald mis-sold
OL,7,Fsolar panels and emergency medical
OL,8,Fbuttons through his companies,
OL,9,FSunpower Renewables Ltd and Proshield
OL,10,FAlarms.
OL,12,FHis businesses pressured customers
OL,13,Finto signing contracts for poor-
OL,14,Fquality work, sometimes causing
OL,15,Fstructural damage to homes.
OL,17,FProshield Alarms falsely promised
OL,18,Fround-the-clock safety with emergency
OL,19,Falert systems, misleading customers
OL,20,Fwith false statements and marketing
OL,21,Fmaterials.
